		<td><b>Re: Why do existing PC emulators suck so bad?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Look, there are some bugs that even DOSBox has. For example, one the MESS team found in both DOSBox, and MESS, is that 0x3C0 bit 5 on the address portion of the register is not emulated. At all. This made it to where some stuff that would run in DOSBox and MESS, would not work on real hardware (e.g. something like the PS/2 Model 70 with the original IBM VGA).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


