		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah, you can't even write a program on most hardware, run it on a machine, and be sure it'll run the same again <em>on the same machine</em>, let alone another machine of the same model, or another PC model/manufacturer, because there can be unpredictable effects. So forget having it run on an emulator and then run exactly the same on hardware. Even hardware fails at this.

		

		</td>
